def: The quality or state of being watery; moisture; humidity.
Pay; reward. [Obs.]In withholding or abridging of the ship or the hire or the wages ofservants. Chaucer.
Of or pertaining to both the sacrum and the hip; as, thesacrosciatic formina formed by the sacrosciatic ligaments whichconnect the sacrum and hip bone.
To pommel; to beat, as with a stick; figuratively, to assail orcriticise in conversation, or in writing. Thackeray.

A curved piece of timber to which the two sides of a ship areunited at the fore end. The lower end of it is scarfed to the keel,and the bowsprit rests upon its upper end. Hence, the forward part ofa vessel; the bow.
A door-keeper; a porter; one who has the care of a publicbuilding, or a building occupied for offices, suites of rooms, etc.
The song thrush. See under Song.
The officer in a religious house who had the care of theinfirmary. [Obs.]
A short bar used by thieves to wrench doors open. [Written alsobettee.]The powerful betty, or the artful picklock. Arbuthnot.
Like, or pertaining to the genus Carabus.
